<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Nulwenu.com">
  <main class="policy-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last Updated: March 1, 2025</em></p>
    <p>
      At SuperCight Domains, we prioritize your privacy while building <em
        >Nulwenu.com</em
      >—your hub for online gaming and coaching. This Privacy Policy explains
      how we collect, use, and protect your data when you explore our site or
      blog.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Personal Information</strong>: Submitting a contact form
        collects your name, email, and message.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Newsletter Sign-Ups</strong>: Joining our newsletter provides us
        your email.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Usage Data</strong>: Google Analytics tracks anonymized data
        like IP addresses, browser type, and page visits.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cookies</strong>: Cookies may be added soon to improve
        functionality—watch for updates.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To reply to your inquiries or feedback.</li>
      <li>To deliver newsletter updates (opt-out available).</li>
      <li>To enhance our site and blog via usage insights.</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We don’t sell or share your data for marketing.</li>
      <li>
        Data may go to providers like Google Analytics, only for operational
        needs.
      </li>
      <li>Legal disclosures may occur if required.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We secure your data with standard measures, though absolute security isn’t
      guaranteed.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may email <a href="mailto:privacy@supercight.com"
        >privacy@supercight.com</a
      > to access, correct, or delete your personal data, or to opt out of newsletters.
      Residents of regions with applicable privacy laws (e.g., California under CCPA,
      EU under GDPR) may also request additional rights, such as opting out of data
      processing, where legally required.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>External links (e.g., blog sources) have their own privacy terms.</p>

    <h2>7. Updates</h2>
    <p>Check “Last Updated” for changes.</p>

    <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@supercight.com">privacy@supercight.com</a>
      or SuperCight Domains, Chicago, IL, USA.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>
